EU referendum: sign up for our experimental mobile alerts

2016-06-22

The Guardian is testing a new type of notification for mobile devices. Here’s how you can take part in our experiment 




Many users of the Guardian’s mobile app get notifications, or “push alerts”, on breaking news stories. You might like to know that the Guardian Mobile Innovation Lab is currently testing a new style of notification, powered by the Chrome web browser.

If you have an Android phone – Samsung included – we hope you’ll 

These are separate from our app notifications, and you don’t have to be an app user to take part in this experiment. 

The Guardian Mobile Innovation Lab is a small innovation team based in the Guardian’s US newsroom. 

